    "body": "# [Security] Neovim affected by GHSA-crm5-rh6j-2c7c — netrw NetrwBookHistSave() code injection via crafted directory name (vim < 9.2.0495)\n\n## Summary\n\nNeovim bundles the netrw plugin (`runtime/pack/dist/opt/netrw/autoload/netrw.vim`) which\ncontains the `s:NetrwBookHistSave()` function vulnerable to code injection via crafted\ndirectory names. The fix from vim 9.2.0495 (commit `f08ab2f4d7d2947c8dd6c179ae08ee6146a2694b`)\nhas not been applied to neovim's bundled netrw.\n\n## Vulnerability Details\n\n- **GHSA**: [GHSA-crm5-rh6j-2c7c](https://github.com/vim/vim/security/advisories/GHSA-crm5-rh6j-2c7c)\n- **Upstream fix (vim)**: 9.2.0495 (commit `f08ab2f4d7d2947c8dd6c179ae08ee6146a2694b`, 2026-05-17)\n- **Affected code**: `runtime/pack/dist/opt/netrw/autoload/netrw.vim` — `s:NetrwBookHistSave()`\n- **Vulnerability type**: CWE-94 — Improper Control of Generation of Code (Code Injection)\n\n## Root Cause\n\nIn `s:NetrwBookHistSave()`, the directory history is serialized to `~/.vim/.netrwhist` using\na single-quoted Vimscript string literal without escaping embedded single quotes:\n\n```vim\n\" runtime/pack/dist/opt/netrw/autoload/netrw.vim line 2938 (neovim HEAD 84d5c5f4b)\ncall setline(lastline,'let g:netrw_dirhist_'.cnt.\"='\".g:netrw_dirhist_{cnt}.\"'\")\n```\n\nIf the directory name contains a single quote `'`, the generated Vimscript breaks out of\nthe string literal. For example, a directory named:\n```\nx'|let g:injected=1|let y='z\n```\nwould generate:\n```vim\nlet g:netrw_dirhist_1='x'|let g:injected=1|let y='z'\n```\n\nWhen `~/.vim/.netrwhist` is later sourced by netrw at startup (via the `VimLeave`\nautocommand `au VimLeave * call s:NetrwBookHistSave()` and `NetrwBookHistRead()`), the\ninjected Vimscript executes with full privileges.\n\n### Attack Scenario\n\n1. An attacker creates a directory with an embedded single-quote followed by Vimscript:\n   ```sh\n   mkdir -p \"target/x'|call system('id > /tmp/pwned')|let y='z\"\n   ```\n2. The victim opens this directory in netrw (`:Explore`) and then quits neovim.\n3. `s:NetrwBookHistSave()` writes the crafted path unescaped to `~/.vim/.netrwhist`.\n4. The next time neovim starts and opens netrw, `NetrwBookHistRead()` sources `.netrwhist`,\n   executing the injected command — **persistent** arbitrary command execution.\n\n## Verification\n\nThe vulnerable pattern is confirmed in neovim HEAD (`84d5c5f4b`):\n\n```\n$ grep -n \"netrw_dirhist_.*cnt.*=.*'\" runtime/pack/dist/opt/netrw/autoload/netrw.vim\n2938:    call setline(lastline,'let g:netrw_dirhist_'.cnt.\"='\".g:netrw_dirhist_{cnt}.\"'\")\n```\n\nThe vim 9.2.0495 fix (`f08ab2f4d7d2947c8dd6c179ae08ee6146a2694b`) has not been applied:\n\n```\n$ git log --all --oneline | grep -i \"9.2.0495\\|NetrwBookHistSave\\|crm5\"\n(no output)\n```\n\n## Suggested Fix\n\nApply the upstream fix from vim 9.2.0495:\n\n```vim\n\" Fixed:\ncall setline(lastline,'let g:netrw_dirhist_'.cnt.'='.string(g:netrw_dirhist_{cnt}))\n```\n\n`string()` properly double-quotes the value and escapes embedded single quotes, so\ndirectory names with `'` safely round-trip through `source`.\n\nOr import the fix as a vim-patch commit:\n- Upstream fix: https://github.com/vim/vim/commit/f08ab2f4d7d2947c8dd6c179ae08ee6146a2694b\n- GHSA: https://github.com/vim/vim/security/advisories/GHSA-crm5-rh6j-2c7c\n",
