            "body": "Thank you for the quick fix (a7d3835)! Since this is a security vulnerability (CWE-94 code injection), would you consider creating a GitHub Security Advisory for neovim to get a CVE assigned? You can draft one from the repository's Security tab — GitHub's CNA can assign a CVE automatically. The upstream vim advisory is GHSA-crm5-rh6j-2c7c; a neovim-specific CVE would help downstream users (distributions, package managers) track and patch accordingly.",
